article.headline: South Florida 62, Rutgers 40
article.story: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- Kentrell Gransberry scored 13 points and grabbed 13 rebounds Wednesday night, leading South Florida to a 62-40 victory over Rutgers. Melvin Buckley had 11 points and Jesus Verdejo scored all 10 of his points in the first half to help the Bulls (11-10, 2-5) build a 20-point halftime lead and win for just the third time in 23 conference games since joining the Big East last season. The loss left Rutgers (8-12, 1-6) alone at the bottom of the Big East standings. The Scarlet Knights have dropped five straight by an average of nearly 17 points and once again were done in by an inability to score. The league's lowest scoring team missed 23 of 30 shots before halftime and were 16-of-58 (27.6 percent) for the game, including 1-of-17 on 3-point attempts. South Florida led 38-18 at the break, pulling away with a 21-7 spurt over the final 11:30 of the opening half. USF lost 15 straight in the conference before upsetting Georgetown in last year's season finale. The Bulls beat Cincinnati at home on Jan. 14 for their second-ever league victory, and viewed Wednesday night as crucial to any hopes they have finishing high enough to earn a spot in the Big East Tournament in March. With Gransberry dominating inside and Verdejo making his first four shots, USF were in control from the start. The Bulls extended the lead to 24 early in the second half and the closest Rutgers got the rest of the way was 18 with seven minutes to go. JR Inman and Ollie Bailey led Rutgers with 10 points apiece. Chris Howard joined Gransberry and Verdejo in double figures for South Florida with 10.
